               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460921-name-1112" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1112" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1112" type="surname" value="TOWERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1112" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN TOWERS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a seaman, and lodge at Mrs. Spurrier's, College—street, Horsley—down—the prisoner came to lodge there last Friday afternoon—I had my chest in the kitchen—it was not locked—I had a jacket, waistcoat, and trowsers in it—I left them in the chest and the prisoner in the house on Friday—I returned home about twelve o'clock—I found I had left my chest unlocked and my clothes were gone—these are my clothes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did you not go with me to fetch my clothes up <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, we were drinking—I did not leave the key in my chest and say you was welcome to anything—you asked if I had any tobacco—I went to my chest and you had an opportunity of seeing what was in it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460921-name-1113" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1113" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1113" type="surname" value="SPURRIER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1113" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH SPURRIER</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner and prosecutor lodged with me—the prosecutor came home and told me of his loss—I went after the prisoner and overtook him—he had these clothes on—I said, "How could you do such a thing, you have got John's clothes on"—he ran away—I called, "Stop thief," ami he was stopped several streets off.</p>
